CNCP v1 23714
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#9396: Transition: custom appear(-active/to) classes stay on the element after transition ends.",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:33.158026+00:00",
  "text": "Transition: custom appear(-active/to) classes stay on the element after transition ends.\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.2.20\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n When using the Transition component, add the property apper= true and add the property appearToClass to wrap a component that uses the v-show directive in the component defaults to false, and then when the component is initialized, change v-show=true, and the class added by the appearToClass property will not disappear on the node all the time\n\n### What is expected?\n\ncorrect\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe appearToClass property remained\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    "scope: transition",
    ":hammer: p3-minor-bug"
  ],
